n=5
P(n,k) = \binom{n}{k} p^k (1-p)^{n-k} \implies P(5,3) = \binom{5}{3} \left ( \frac{1}{2} \right )^3 \left ( \frac{1}{2} \right )^2 = \frac{5}{16}
P(5,3) + P(5,4) + P(5,5) = \frac{10+5+1}{32} = \frac{1}{2}
